common_name_other: bushy lippia, honeyherb, Aztec Sweet Herb
medicinal: Traditionally used to treat coughs, asthma, and bronchitis (expectorant). Very long literary history.
food: Noted for sweet taste (contains hernandulcin, a very sweet sesquiterpenoid), but does not apprear to have been refinied or processed as a sweetener. Also contains high concentration of camphor, and so should not be eaten in large quantities, though some sources mention chewing the leaves or adding them to salads.
